Heat broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and very thinly
slice @yellow onion{2%units}. Pick @thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; mince
leaves until you have @thyme leaves{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4), reserving a few whole
leaves for garnish. Trim ends from @demi-baguette{1%unit}; slice crosswise into 6
equal-size rounds (12 rounds for 4 servings). Halve @lemon{1%unit}.
In a #small bowl{}, combine juice from whole lemon, a large drizzle of
@olive oil{}, and @dijon mustard{2%teaspoon} to taste. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}; set aside.

Heat a #large pot{} over medium-high heat; add a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}
and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Add onions and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until onions are slightly softened and browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.
Stir in @water{1/4%cup}, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan.
Cook, without stirring, ~{8-10%minutes} more. Add another @water{1/4%cup},
scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan; cook, stirring occasionally,
until deeply browned and caramelized, ~{8-10%minutes} more.

> If onions start to burn, add a splash of water.

To #pot{} with caramelized onions, add @sherry vinegar{5%teaspoon},
minced thyme, @sugar{1%tablespoon}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook until deeply
browned and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @mushroom stock concentrate{3%unit} and
@water{3%cups}. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until
flavors meld, ~{3-5%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, halve, core, and thinly slice half the @Hudson River Fruit RubyFrost
apple{1%unit} into half-moons. In a #large bowl{}, toss apple slices and
@mixed greens{2%ounce} with as much dressing as you like. Season with salt and
pepper.

Place baguette slices on a #baking sheet{} and top evenly with
@gruyère cheese{1/2%cup}. Broil on top rack until cheese is melted and bubbly,
~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide soup between bowls. Top with gruyère toasts. Garnish with reserved thyme
leaves as desired. Serve with salad on the side.